# Cross-OS line-ending safety. Git-for-Windows defaults to core.autocrlf=true, which would check
# out every text file with CRLF — and CRLF breaks sh scripts (`\r: command not found`): the git
# hooks (.githooks/), scripts/setup-hooks.sh, and db/backup.sh (which runs on the Linux VM).
# `eol=lf` pins LF in every working tree, on every OS, regardless of local git config.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Windows-native script types would need CRLF (none in the repo today; kept for completeness).
*.bat text eol=crlf
*.ps1 text eol=crlf

# Binary assets — never normalize.
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif binary
*.ico binary
*.pdf binary
*.mp4 binary
*.pkl binary
*.joblib binary
*.zip binary
